Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright.dev/blob/main/java/versioned_docs/version-stable/accessibility-testing.mdx

This snippet demonstrates how to perform a full-page accessibility scan using Playwright and the `axe-core/playwright` Java library. It initializes Playwright, navigates to a specified URL, runs `AxeBuilder.analyze()` to detect violations across the entire page, and asserts that no violations are found using JUnit 5's `assertEquals` method.

